# Agent Rules for BRain-D-450mm

- Always use plan mode for complex changes
- Always ask me permission to implement any plans
- Suggest me better gemini model for each plan implementation
- Delete intermediate files generated by the agent automatically
- Export git commit extraction logs directly to Docs without generating intermediate scripts. Always generate a log_github_lastrun.csv everytime.
- Git commits MUST be extremely verbose and detailed. Use a 3-digit Sequential Build Numbers prefix for the subject line (e.g., "[Build #001] type: concise summary"), followed by a blank line, and then a comprehensive multi-line description explaining the "why" and "what" of the changes, detailing every modified file and the rationale. Keep incrementing the build number using three digits padded with zeros.
- Update requirements.txt if you detect a new package
- Always fetch to origin
